.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a basic UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that executes commands read from standard input.

It implements basic shell functionality including command execution, built-in commands, and PATH resolution.

.SH FEATURES
The shell supports:
.TP
\fBInteractive mode\fR
Displays a prompt and waits for user input
.TP
\fBNon-interactive mode\fR
Reads and executes commands from a pipe or file
.TP
\fBBuilt-in commands\fR
exit, env

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit [status]
Exit the shell with optional exit status
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode:
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) ls
main.c shell.c README.md
($) exit
.fi
.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.nf
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
-rw-r--r-- 1 user user 200 Nov 12 main.c
.fi

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the exit status of the last command executed, or the status specified with exit.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2), fork(2)

.SH AUTHORS
Shaden Khaled, Own Algarni
